HEADWORD: chummy
<hw>chummy</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>having the relationship
of friends or pals.</def> <mark>[colloquial]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> matey, pally, palsy-walsy.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>associated on close terms.</def>
<mark>[informal]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> thick(predicate).</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

